   t = (xb - mu) / (s/sqrt(n)) = (9.9341 - 10) / (1.7404/√20) = -0.1693

4. p-value:
   df = 19
   two-sided p = 2*(1 - F_t(19)(|t|)) ≈ 0.8660

5. Decision:
   p = 0.8660 > alp = 0.05 → fail to reject H0

6. Conclusion:
   At the 0.05 level, there is no significant evidence that the sample mean differs from mu = 10.
